I think this move is a mistake. Although the correct plan is a king's side attack, as black hasn't advanced the f, g or h pawns, it will be hard to open a file there. I think best was to secure the d pawn with Ne2, may followed by B-d2-c3 and Rd1, and then use the Nf3 to go back to the old plan of attacking h7 with the Ng5 and queen on d3 or h5
